cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a method for imitation learning in robotic control, which involves learning from high-dimensional, continuous observations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions experiments in Box2D, Atari, and MuJoCo, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to cs.CV and cs.SY. However, since the paper focuses on a specific method for imitation learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
